      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2021-02-23</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2021-03-16T11:35:48Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text>
            <![CDATA[ <p><b>Ensuring Quality Care for </b><b>O</b><b>ur Veterans Act</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to contract with a nonfederal organization to conduct a quality management review of hospital care or medical services furnished by each Veterans Health Administration (VHA) provider whose license was terminated by a state licensing board based upon care or services provided in a non-VHA facility.</p> <p>If a review determines that the standard of care was not met, the VA shall notify the individual who received such care or services.</p>]]>
          </text>
          <updateDate>2021-02-23T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
